In this project I was not familiar with thr getopt() and make check, 
especially when scripting tests into a make file, so I looked up these
tutorials and examples on how to utilize them. (The references are listed 
below), everything else I refered to the hw/labs I did in cs33 and cs35l

	The test cases I tested where testing the following:
./lab0 --input in.txt 
./lab0 --input.txt in.txt --output out.txt 
./lab0 --segfault
./lab0 --segfault --catch

For the Make file the default option make should
only produce the executable lab0

check will test the four cases above, I used a counter to check
whether each case will pass or not and if all case pass, then
the last line of the output will say "all smoke test passed"

dist will produce the tarball with the following files:
lab0.c
part5backtrace.png
part6nullptr.png
Makefile
README

